"ADVENTURE CRAFTS" "CRAFTING PATTERNS"

Some items - often found in adventures - can teach you new crafting recipes
for as long as you own them. These recipes behave slightly differently from
other recipes; you cannot get crafting information on them unless you have
the item, and they can scale higher than level 100. They often also require a
specific ability, and sometimes a minimum Crafting level.

These factors limit the level of the resulting item:
  The level range of the item itself.
  Your Crafting level.
  
You can see the scaling level range of the item a recipe creates on its 'info'
(for example, 'forge info ring').

See also: SCALABLE CRAFTS
