"SCALABLE CRAFTS" "SCALABLE CRAFTING" "CRAFTING SCALABLES"

Many craftable items (including things made with brew, craft, forge, and sew)
are scalable, which means they change in power and attributes based on the
level and skills of the person.

For most recipes, the level of the resulting item will be the lowest of:
  The upper end of the level range of the ability that gives the recipe.
  Your level in the ability's skill (usually Trade).
  Your Crafting level.

For example, the arming sword from Iron Blades cannot be higher than level 75,
since this ability has a level range of 55-75.

Recipes which come from crafting patterns follow slightly different rules - see
HELP CRAFTING PATTERNS for more information.

If a craftable item is made superior, it will scale higher even at the same
level.

The identify command will help you determine if two crafted items are different
in power, even if they have the same name.

See also: CRAFTING PATTERNS, CRAFTING LEVEL, IDENTIFY, SUPERIOR
